FBIS3-3423 "drchi054_a_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Journalists Must Follow `Necessary Formalities' OW2103124594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1236 GMT 21 Mar 94 OW2103124594 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, March 21 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman said here today that it was improper for foreign journalists to cover news in China without going through necessary formalities. He made the statement while commenting on a report that an AGENCE FRANCE PRESSE reporter who was conducting news coverage activities at the Tiananmen Square was stopped and had his film exposed. The spokesman also said that two Chinese women were stopped by other citizens for disturbing public order this morning.
